                    	<ul>
                    		<li>
                    			Bachelor’s degree from an accredited university with concentration in Human Resources, Business or Marketing
                    		</li>
                    		<li>
                    			3-5 years of demonstrated recruitment/talent acquisition experience
                    		</li>
                    		<li>
                    			Experience as a strategic partner working with hiring managers and executives to clarify job specifications and optimize job descriptions
                    		</li>
                    		<li>
                    			Partner with HR Director and business managers to fill current hiring needs and identify future needs
                    		</li>
                    		<li>
                    			Manage the offer/negotiation process, working with the HR team, hiring manager, the candidate
                    		</li>
                    		<li>
                    			Facilitate feedback from hiring managers and other interviewers after each interview
                    		</li>
                    		<li>
                    			Represent the organization at job fairs, conferences and in other relevant organizations to attract new talent
                    		</li>
                    		<li>
                    			Participate and contribute to HR organization and Recruiting department special projects
                    		</li>
                    		<li>
                    			Understand the organizational culture and needs as well as the importance of following operational and process requirements
                    		</li>
                    		<li>
